  praktiske_verktøy
  abstract_AI_konfig
  astrée_analysator
  polyspace_analysator
  clang_analyzer
  coverity_analyse
}

// Semantic direction:
// abstrakt_interpretasjon: Cousot & Cousot (1977) — run programs over abstract domains to
//   derive sound over-approximations of all possible runtime states.
// galois_forbindelsen: a pair (α, γ) where α: Concrete → Abstract, γ: Abstract → Concrete,
//   with α(c) ⊑ a ⟺ c ⊆ γ(a) — the core soundness condition.
// fortegns_domene: abstract values {−, 0, +, ⊤} — cheap and useful for sign analysis.
// intervall_domene: represent values as intervals [l, u] — powerful but costly joins.
// widening_operasjon: accelerates convergence by extrapolating; may lose precision.
// narrowing_operasjon: recovers precision after widening; used in a second pass.
// polyhedron_domene: linear arithmetic constraints over multiple variables — very expressive.
// andersen_analyse: inclusion-based points-to analysis — cubic in program size.
// steensgaard_analyse: unification-based — near-linear but less precise than Andersen.
// astrée_analysator: verifies absence of runtime errors in safety-critical C code (Airbus A380).
// taint_domene: tracks untrusted data flow — used in security analysis for injection detection.

// Primitive flow:
// konkret: {x ∈ ℤ | program kan nå dette punktet med x}
// abstrakt: x ∈ [0, ∞) (intervall som over-approksimerer alle mulige verdier)
// analyse: kjør program med abstrakt domene til fast punkt nås

